To: C++ administrative mailing list
Message c++std-admin-195

We have a lot of organizing to do before the Kona meeting, if everything is to
go smoothly.  There's need for specific volunteers.

Please post to -admin any planning issues that you see I've omitted ...
Then we'll post the revised version to -all to get any further volunteers needed.

Before Kona:
__ US Public Comment completion: complete the Response, do a meeting vote in Kona 
__ Membership checks; each WG21 delegation in writing from the national body
__ Preparing "view-foils" - Plum is providing on-screen projection from PC, so any
   document that MS Word can display in 24-point type (8 lines x 40?) is probably
   adequately visible; ordinary overhead projector will be there too
__ Plan seating by subgroups; allows quick "caucuses" during full session

At Kona:
